cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with object counting, which is a common problem in computer vision. The paper proposes a new method for object counting with incomplete annotations, which is a sub-problem of object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for object detection, which involves learning from incomplete annotations. This makes it relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on two datasets, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM).
